{"page": "Morrowind:Souls", "section": "0", "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The following is a list of the <a href=\"/wiki/Morrowind:Soul_Gems\" title=\"Morrowind:Soul Gems\">soul gems</a> in addition to which <a href=\"/wiki/Morrowind:Creatures\" title=\"Morrowind:Creatures\">creatures</a> will fit in them (creatures will fit into higher quality soul gems as well if you don't have the correct type). Petty, lesser and common soul gems can be bought from restocking merchants and found on random creatures throughout the world. Note that not all variants of creatures are included in the below table as are those with no soul value. Also note that, unlike Daggerfall, the souls in soul gems can never be released. \n</p><p>For souls in the expansion packs, please see <a href=\"/wiki/Tribunal:Souls\" title=\"Tribunal:Souls\">Tribunal:Souls</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Bloodmoon:Souls\" title=\"Bloodmoon:Souls\">Bloodmoon:Souls</a>.\n</p>\n<div style=\"display:inline-table\">\n<table class=\"vtop wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th colspan=\"3\">Petty Soul Gem <small>Misc_Soulgem_Petty</small><br />\n<p>Max Soul strength: 30\n</p>\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width:3em\">5\n</th>\n<td style=\"width:13em\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Morrowind:Mudcrab\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Morrowind:Mudcrab\">Diseased Mudcrab</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Morrowind:Mudcrab\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Morrowind:Mudcrab\">Mudcrab</a></li></ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:13em\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Morrowind:Slaughterfish\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Morrowind:Slaughterfish\">Old Blue Fin</a></li></ul>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>8\n</th>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Morrowind:Kwama_Worker\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Morrowind:Kwama Worker\">Diseased Kwama Worker</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Morrowind:Kwama_Worker\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Morrowind:Kwama Worker\">Kwama Worker</a></li></ul>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>10\n</th>\n<td>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wi